<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1143a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BTH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Birch</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-28T16:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Has declaration of war against Germany, or other decree indicating that a
                            state of war exists, been issued by Portuguese Government? If so, report
                            fully by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>